===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# A fragment of a human expression that is repeated by somebody else. Most often a quotation is taken from {{l|en|literature}} or {{l|en|speech}}, but also scenes from a {{l|en|movie}}, elements of a {{l|en|painting}}, a passage of music, etc., may be quoted.
#: {{syn|en|quote|citation}}
#: {{ux|en|"Where they burn books, they will also burn people" is a famous '''quotation''' from Heinrich Heine.}}
# The act of naming a [[price]]; the price that has been quoted.
#: {{ux|en|Let's get a '''quotation''' for repairing the roof before we decide whether it's worth doing.}}
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[quota]], a [[share]].<ref>{{R:Webster 1913|Quotation}}</ref>

